trans-unit.source: Provides data for the **WindowsAuthentication_OnAuthenticate** event.
trans-unit.target: Proporciona datos para el evento **WindowsAuthentication_OnAuthenticate**.

trans-unit.source: This class cannot be inherited.
trans-unit.target: Esta clase no puede heredarse.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.Security.WindowsAuthenticationEventArgs> class is used to supply event values to the **WindowsAuthentication_OnAuthenticate** event and to enable you to specify a custom Windows identity for the current request.
trans-unit.target: El <xref:System.Web.Security.WindowsAuthenticationEventArgs> clase se utiliza para proporcionar valores de evento para el **WindowsAuthentication_OnAuthenticate** eventos y que le permite especificar una identidad de Windows personalizada para la solicitud actual.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.Security.WindowsAuthenticationModule> constructs a <xref:System.Web.Security.WindowsAuthenticationEventArgs> object using the Windows identity supplied by IIS and the current <xref:System.Web.HttpContext> and passes it to the **WindowsAuthentication_OnAuthenticate** event.
trans-unit.target: El <xref:System.Web.Security.WindowsAuthenticationModule> construye una <xref:System.Web.Security.WindowsAuthenticationEventArgs> utilizando la identidad de Windows proporcionada por IIS y actual del objeto <xref:System.Web.HttpContext> y lo pasa a la **WindowsAuthentication_OnAuthenticate** eventos.

trans-unit.source: You can use the <xref:System.Web.Security.WindowsAuthenticationEventArgs.User%2A> property of the <xref:System.Web.Security.WindowsAuthenticationEventArgs> object supplied to the **WindowsAuthentication_OnAuthenticate** event to set the <xref:System.Web.HttpContext.User%2A> property of the current <xref:System.Web.HttpContext> to a custom <xref:System.Security.Principal.IPrincipal> object.
trans-unit.target: Puede usar el <xref:System.Web.Security.WindowsAuthenticationEventArgs.User%2A> propiedad de la <xref:System.Web.Security.WindowsAuthenticationEventArgs> objeto proporcionado a la **WindowsAuthentication_OnAuthenticate** eventos para establecer el <xref:System.Web.HttpContext.User%2A> propiedad del elemento actual <xref:System.Web.HttpContext> a una personalizada <xref:System.Security.Principal.IPrincipal> objeto.

trans-unit.source: If you do not specify a value for the <xref:System.Web.Security.WindowsAuthenticationEventArgs.User%2A> property during the **WindowsAuthentication_OnAuthenticate** event, the Windows identity supplied by IIS is used as the identity for the current request.
trans-unit.target: Si no especifica un valor para el <xref:System.Web.Security.WindowsAuthenticationEventArgs.User%2A> propiedad durante la **WindowsAuthentication_OnAuthenticate** eventos, las ventanas de identidad proporcionada por IIS se usa como la identidad de la solicitud actual.

trans-unit.source: If IIS uses anonymous authentication, then the <xref:System.Web.Security.WindowsAuthenticationEventArgs.Identity%2A> property is set to the identity returned by the <xref:System.Security.Principal.WindowsIdentity.GetAnonymous%2A> method.
trans-unit.target: Si IIS utiliza la autenticación anónima, la <xref:System.Web.Security.WindowsAuthenticationEventArgs.Identity%2A> propiedad se establece en la identidad devuelta por la <xref:System.Security.Principal.WindowsIdentity.GetAnonymous%2A> método.

trans-unit.source: The **WindowsAuthentication_OnAuthenticate** event is raised only when the authentication <xref:System.Web.Configuration.AuthenticationSection.Mode%2A> is set to <xref:System.Web.Configuration.AuthenticationMode.Windows> and the <xref:System.Web.Security.WindowsAuthenticationModule> is an active HTTP module for the application.
trans-unit.target: El **WindowsAuthentication_OnAuthenticate** evento se desencadena únicamente cuando la autenticación <xref:System.Web.Configuration.AuthenticationSection.Mode%2A> se establece en <xref:System.Web.Configuration.AuthenticationMode.Windows> y <xref:System.Web.Security.WindowsAuthenticationModule> es un módulo HTTP activo para la aplicación.

trans-unit.source: The following code example uses the **WindowsAuthentication_OnAuthenticate** event to set the <xref:System.Web.HttpContext.User%2A> property of the current <xref:System.Web.HttpContext> to a custom <xref:System.Security.Principal.IPrincipal> object.
trans-unit.target: El siguiente ejemplo de código utiliza el **WindowsAuthentication_OnAuthenticate** eventos para establecer el <xref:System.Web.HttpContext.User%2A> propiedad del elemento actual <xref:System.Web.HttpContext> a una personalizada <xref:System.Security.Principal.IPrincipal> objeto.

trans-unit.source: Gets the <see cref="T:System.Web.HttpContext" /> object for the current HTTP request.
trans-unit.target: Obtiene el objeto <see cref="T:System.Web.HttpContext" /> de la solicitud HTTP actual.

trans-unit.source: The <see cref="T:System.Web.HttpContext" /> object for the current HTTP request.
trans-unit.target: Objeto <see cref="T:System.Web.HttpContext" /> de la solicitud HTTP actual.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.HttpContext> provides access to <xref:System.Web.HttpContext.Request%2A>, <xref:System.Web.HttpContext.Response%2A>, and <xref:System.Web.HttpContext.User%2A> objects for the current request.
trans-unit.target: El <xref:System.Web.HttpContext> proporciona acceso a <xref:System.Web.HttpContext.Request%2A>, <xref:System.Web.HttpContext.Response%2A>, y <xref:System.Web.HttpContext.User%2A> objetos para la solicitud actual.
